                     /synonym="maltose/maltodextrin-binding protein"
                     /note="Maltose/maltodextrin-binding periplasmic protein
                     precursor (MalE / MBP), E. coli K12 malE; UniProt P0AEX9,
                     396 aa. As stored this is the full PRECURSOR: an N-terminal
                     26-aa signal peptide (aa 1-26) followed by the 370-aa
                     mature protein (aa 27-396). Periplasmic
                     maltose/maltodextrin transport component; widely
                     re-purposed as an N-terminal fusion partner that strongly
                     enhances soluble expression of its passenger and binds
                     amylose resin (eluted with maltose) for affinity
                     purification."
